subSubSection.paragraph:
Female terminalia (
Figs. 243–245
): Sternite 7 with rounded (rarely slightly arrow-shaped) posteromedial process flanked by deep, partially membranous emargination on each side, microtrichia of posteromedial third of sclerite greatly enlarged, directed medially, posteriorly, and sometimes anteriorly (pattern variable). Tergite 10 + cerci with a pair of long bristles near middle plus several shorter setulae.
